HEADWORD: Fireplace
<hw>Fire"place`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The part a chimney
appropriated to the fire; a hearth; -- usually an open recess in a wall,
in which a fire may be built.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

